	<exercise>
	<title>Avoiding Common Mistakes</title>
	<statement>
		<p>If <m>A\cdot B = 0</m> what must <m>A</m> or <m>B</m> be equal to? If <m>C \cdot D = 1</m> can you come to a similiar conclusion?</p>
	</statement>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
	<title>Solving Rational Equations</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Identify the domain of the equation. Then solve each rational equation for <m>x</m>. Show all your work as a sequence of equations.</p>
		<ol labels="a" cols="2">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{2x+1}{4} = 0</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{4}{2x+1} = 0</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{4x}{2x+1} = 0</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{4x}{2x+1} = 1</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{4}{x+5}-2 = 1</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{5}{2x-8} -3  = -\frac{7}{x-1}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle 3 - \frac{2}{x+1} = \frac{4}{x^2-1}</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \frac{x+1}{x+2}-1 = \frac{x+2}{x-4}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</statement>
	<answer>
	<ol labels="a" cols="2">
			<li><m>\displaystyle x=-1/2</m></li>
			<li>No solutions.</li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x = 0</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x = 1/2</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x = -11/3</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x = 5/2, \, 17/3</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x=5/3</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x=-5, \, 0</m></li>
		</ol>
	</answer>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
	<title>Solving Radical Equations</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Solve each radical equation for <m>x</m>. Show all your work as a sequence of equations. Be sure to check your results for extraneous solutions.</p>
		<ol labels="a" cols="2">
			<li><m>\displaystyle \sqrt{1-x} = 1</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \sqrt{1-x} = -1</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \sqrt{1-x} - 1 = x</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \sqrt{1-x} +2= x</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \sqrt[3]{1-x} = -1</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle \sqrt{x+1} = 2- \sqrt{x+2}</m></li>
		</ol>
	</statement>
	<answer>
		<ol labels="a" >
			<li><m>\displaystyle x=0</m></li>
			<li>No solutions.</li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x=0</m></li>
			<li>No solutions.</li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x = 2</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x=-7/16</m></li>
		</ol>
	</answer>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
	<title>Solving Absolute Value Equations</title>
	<statement>
		<p>Solve each absolute value equation for <m>x</m>. Show all your work as a sequence of equations.</p>
		<ol> labels="a" >
			<li><m>\displaystyle |2x+1| = 3</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle |2x+1| = -3</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle |2x-1| = x</m></li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle |2x+1| = x</m></li>
		</ol>
	</statement>
	<answer>
		<ol> labels="a" >
			<li><m>\displaystyle x = -2, \, 1</m></li>
			<li>No solutions. The left side of the equation is never negative.</li>
			<li><m>\displaystyle x = 1/3, \, 1</m></li>
			<li>No solutions. Try solving the equations <m>2x+1 = x</m> and <m>2x+1 = -x</m>. Why do these not lead to solutions?</li>
		</ol>
	</answer>
	</exercise>

